criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

        participants with chronic low back pain

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. low back pain accompanied by specific pathological conditions, such as an
             infection,inflammation, rheumatoid arthritis, fracture, or tumor;

          2. a self-reported history of malignancy, vertigo, stroke, or other condition that may
             impair postural stability;

          3. a history of low back surgery with an implant;

          4. pregnancy or plans to become pregnant during the course of the study;

          5. having received concurrent treatment for low back pain by another health care
             professional
